1
00:00:01,235 --> 00:00:03,704
( Joseph gasping )

2
00:00:03,737 --> 00:00:05,372
Dio: Just as I thought,

3
00:00:05,405 --> 00:00:08,375
joseph’s blood suits me well.

4
00:00:08,408 --> 00:00:09,609
( Jotaro growls )

5
00:00:09,643 --> 00:00:11,712
Dio: It’s like it was
meant to be mine

6
00:00:11,745 --> 00:00:13,580
from the very beginning.

7
00:00:13,614 --> 00:00:16,283
It’s far more intense than
anything i’ve ever felt before!

8
00:00:16,316 --> 00:00:20,387
This sensation is
absolutely incredible!

9
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:22,656
( Laughing )

10
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:28,729
A century ago, this body
belonged to Jonathan joestar,

11
00:00:28,762 --> 00:00:30,697
and now these hands have feasted

12
00:00:30,731 --> 00:00:32,866
on the blood
of his grandson, Joseph!

13
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:36,904
but it was you, jotaro,
who so thoughtfully led me here.

14
00:00:36,937 --> 00:00:39,807
your ancestor
must be rolling in his grave.

15
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:41,975
You joestars have
always been a nuisance,

16
00:00:42,009 --> 00:00:45,646
so I think the time has come to
put you self-righteous cretins

17
00:00:45,679 --> 00:00:47,681
in your proper place,
beneath my boot!

18
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,683
In the end, jotaro,

19
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:51,885
it would appear
that the joestars’s destiny

20
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:55,256
is to facilitate
my ascension to perfection!

21
00:00:55,289 --> 00:00:56,891
( Laughing )

22
00:00:58,659 --> 00:01:00,494
Jotaro: Why, you...

23
00:01:00,527 --> 00:01:03,430
( Dio laughing )

24
00:01:03,463 --> 00:01:04,431
( Jotaro gasps )

25
00:01:04,464 --> 00:01:06,466
♪

26
00:01:15,008 --> 00:01:16,910
Old man.

27
00:01:16,944 --> 00:01:19,380
Joseph: You have to stay calm.

28
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:23,884
From here on, no matter what
dio does to me, keep your cool.

29
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:26,453
Focus. Tempting as it may be,

30
00:01:26,486 --> 00:01:29,422
never allow yourself
to succumb to anger.

31
00:01:29,456 --> 00:01:31,825
Don’t worry about my fate,
jotaro.

32
00:01:31,859 --> 00:01:34,395
i’ve accepted
that it was meant to be.

33
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:35,729
Jotaro: Wait a sec.

34
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:38,999
That’s his soul? But how?

35
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:43,003
Joseph: Kakyoin deciphered
the mystery of dio’s stand,

36
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:45,805
and I imparted
that knowledge to you.

37
00:01:45,839 --> 00:01:48,809
Had we attacked dio together
before learning his secret,

38
00:01:48,842 --> 00:01:52,412
he would have been able
to easily kill all of us.

39
00:01:52,446 --> 00:01:56,016
You now have the ability
to move while time is frozen,

40
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:58,752
but you only have
two or three seconds.

41
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,954
Make sure you use
that time wisely.

42
00:02:00,988 --> 00:02:04,391
Remember what I told you,
jotaro.

43
00:02:04,424 --> 00:02:06,359
You mustn’t lose your head.

44
00:02:06,393 --> 00:02:08,795
If you lose control,
it’ll only backfire.

45
00:02:08,829 --> 00:02:12,566
Keep your emotions in check
when you face off with dio.

46
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:15,635
Jotaro...

47
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:17,237
( Jotaro gasps )

48
00:02:17,271 --> 00:02:20,541
joseph: It’s been
quite the journey, eh, my boy,

49
00:02:20,574 --> 00:02:22,743
an unforgettable adventure.

50
00:02:22,776 --> 00:02:25,612
Call me crazy.
( Chuckles )

51
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:28,616
But our time together
was a lot of fun,

52
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:31,452
more fun than i’ve had
in a long time.

53
00:02:40,861 --> 00:02:43,731
Jotaro: That was real, right?

54
00:02:43,764 --> 00:02:44,865
Dio: Hey!

55
00:02:44,898 --> 00:02:48,568
What are you looking at,
jotaro?!

56
00:02:50,571 --> 00:02:52,540
( Blood flowing )

57
00:02:52,573 --> 00:02:54,542
♪

58
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:02,182
Jotaro: You bastard!

59
00:03:02,216 --> 00:03:04,185
Dio: He’s been sucked dry.

60
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:06,721
( Laughing )

61
00:03:09,723 --> 00:03:12,693
Jotaro: I know you said
to keep my emotions in check,

62
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:15,696
but screw that!
He just crossed the line!

63
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:17,798
There’s not a person
on the planet

64
00:03:17,831 --> 00:03:19,900
who could stay calm
after seeing that!

65
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,935
Dio: This fight
has come to an end!

66
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:30,411
♪

67
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:32,446
( Singing in Japanese )

68
00:04:38,478 --> 00:04:40,447
( Ticking slows, stops )

69
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,315
( Music stops )

70
00:04:42,349 --> 00:04:44,351
( Footsteps echoing )

71
00:04:48,822 --> 00:04:51,558
( Singing in Japanese resumes )

72
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:53,828
( Star platinum yelling )

73
00:04:53,861 --> 00:04:56,964
( The world yelling )

74
00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:58,999
♪

75
00:05:09,543 --> 00:05:13,514
the world!
Bring time to a halt!

76
00:05:13,547 --> 00:05:15,783
( Yells )

77
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:19,186
One second, two seconds,

78
00:05:19,219 --> 00:05:20,787
and three seconds.

79
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,656
Now four...

80
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:25,792
- ( Gasps )
- ( Stands yelling )

81
00:05:26,894 --> 00:05:28,429
( Dio yells )

82
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:30,197
( Star platinum yelling )

83
00:05:30,230 --> 00:05:33,567
Dio: Five seconds. Interesting.

84
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,203
Six seconds. My, my.

85
00:05:36,236 --> 00:05:37,537
( Jotaro gasps )

86
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,541
Dio: This makes seven seconds.

87
00:05:41,575 --> 00:05:43,610
My power grows exponentially!

88
00:05:43,644 --> 00:05:46,547
I can stop time for even longer.

89
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:48,415
But as for you, jotaro,

90
00:05:48,448 --> 00:05:51,651
you wasted the opportunity
you had to move.

91
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:54,655
gambling on getting me
two seconds before time resumed

92
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:55,923
was all for naught.

93
00:05:55,956 --> 00:05:58,725
What a miscalculation.

94
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:00,227
( Chuckles )

95
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,796
I feel so marvelous,
I could serenade the world!

96
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:06,434
The moment i’ve dreamed of
for so long is finally upon us.

97
00:06:06,466 --> 00:06:08,601
Eight seconds have passed.

98
00:06:08,635 --> 00:06:12,239
I’ve been an immortal being
for an entire century...

99
00:06:12,272 --> 00:06:14,341
- ( Squelching )
- But never in my wildest dreams

100
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:17,677
could I have imagined i’d feel
something this exhilarating!

101
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,313
( Laughs )

102
00:06:19,346 --> 00:06:22,382
The blood of the joestars
courses through my veins!

103
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,285
The blood of the joestars

104
00:06:24,318 --> 00:06:26,253
- courses through my veins!
- Jotaro: Damn it.

105
00:06:26,286 --> 00:06:28,488
Guess you were right,
after all, old man.

106
00:06:28,522 --> 00:06:31,525
My stupid temper got me
in a shit-ton of trouble.

107
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:32,893
For christ’s sake.

108
00:06:32,926 --> 00:06:34,694
No, this isn’t the end!

109
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:38,398
He still hasn’t faced
the full force of my rage!

110
00:06:38,432 --> 00:06:39,733
Dio: Nine seconds total,

111
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:42,369
that’s how long
my power lasted just now.

112
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:45,538
Yes, perhaps nine seconds

113
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:48,909
is the new extent of my stand’s
extraordinary power.

114
00:06:48,942 --> 00:06:50,744
Jotaro: You bastard.

115
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:53,380
( Dio yelling )

116
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:56,783
( Jotaro yells )

117
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:01,355
Dio: Now to unleash
all of my stand’s power!

118
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:04,925
Jotaro, weren’t you mumbling
something about being angry?!

119
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:07,327
is this
all the power you possess?!

120
00:07:09,196 --> 00:07:11,498
( The world yelling )

121
00:07:11,532 --> 00:07:13,200
Muda!

122
00:07:16,637 --> 00:07:19,707
Dio: And now I shall administer
the killing blow!

123
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:22,610
here it is,
my final dance with time!

124
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:27,614
Nine more seconds,
that’s all you have left!

125
00:07:27,648 --> 00:07:30,618
Prepare to die! The world!

126
00:07:30,651 --> 00:07:32,887
( Ticking slows, stops )

127
00:07:39,393 --> 00:07:42,363
( Chuckles )

128
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,798
One second.

129
00:07:44,832 --> 00:07:45,800
( Jotaro gasps )

130
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,935
Dio: Two seconds.

131
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,403
Three seconds.

132
00:07:49,436 --> 00:07:50,837
narrator:
Jotaro couldn’t figure out

133
00:07:50,871 --> 00:07:55,309
why dio had suddenly vanished
amidst the standstill...

134
00:07:55,342 --> 00:07:56,944
Dio: Four seconds.

135
00:07:56,977 --> 00:08:00,180
Narrator: But he pushed
the thoughts out of his mind.

136
00:08:00,214 --> 00:08:03,517
No matter what sinister plot
dio was hatching,

137
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:06,653
no matter what unholy attack
he attempted to unleash,

138
00:08:06,687 --> 00:08:10,191
jotaro had
only two seconds to respond,

139
00:08:10,224 --> 00:08:13,527
only two seconds to drive
star platinum’s fists into dio

140
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,795
once and for all!

141
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:17,230
Dio: Five seconds.

142
00:08:17,264 --> 00:08:20,567
Jotaro: I’ve had just about
enough of this neon vampire.

143
00:08:20,601 --> 00:08:23,337
The next time I see
that goddamn face of his,

144
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:26,607
i’m gonna freakin’ lose it
and beat him into the ground.

145
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,609
Dio: Six seconds.

146
00:08:28,642 --> 00:08:30,444
Jotaro: That’s right, dio.

147
00:08:30,477 --> 00:08:32,212
Come and get it.

148
00:08:32,246 --> 00:08:35,716
- Dio: Seven seconds.
- ( Jotaro gasps )

149
00:08:35,749 --> 00:08:40,687
Dio: I’m going
to roll all over you!

150
00:08:40,721 --> 00:08:42,423
( Jotaro groans )

151
00:08:42,456 --> 00:08:44,191
( Growls )

152
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:47,627
( Star platinum yelling )

153
00:08:47,661 --> 00:08:50,697
Dio: It’s too late!
Time to die!

154
00:08:50,731 --> 00:08:53,701
( The world yelling )

155
00:08:53,734 --> 00:08:56,704
( Star platinum yelling )

156
00:08:56,737 --> 00:08:58,739
( The world yelling )

157
00:08:58,772 --> 00:08:59,806
Dio: Eight seconds!

158
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,842
( Yells )

159
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:05,145
I’ll obliterate you!

160
00:09:05,179 --> 00:09:07,848
Jotaro: Ora!

161
00:09:07,881 --> 00:09:09,850
♪

162
00:09:11,785 --> 00:09:13,754
Dio: Nine seconds.

163
00:09:15,756 --> 00:09:17,558
I did it.

164
00:09:17,591 --> 00:09:20,160
It’s over.

165
00:09:20,194 --> 00:09:23,497
The world has defeated
star platinum.

166
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:26,166
my stand is
more powerful than his.

167
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,668
I am immortal.

168
00:09:27,701 --> 00:09:30,504
I am everlasting.

169
00:09:30,537 --> 00:09:32,672
( Laughs )

170
00:09:32,706 --> 00:09:35,242
Stand power!

171
00:09:35,275 --> 00:09:38,545
( Laughs )

172
00:09:38,579 --> 00:09:40,581
now there is
incontrovertible proof

173
00:09:40,614 --> 00:09:44,184
that no one on this miserable
planet is stronger than me.

174
00:09:44,218 --> 00:09:46,520
You loathsome humans,

175
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:50,957
I shall rule over your pathetic
species until the end of time.

176
00:09:50,991 --> 00:09:53,594
Now bow before my wisdom
and power!

177
00:09:53,627 --> 00:09:55,529
Ten seconds!

178
00:09:55,562 --> 00:09:57,531
( Laughs )

179
00:09:57,564 --> 00:09:59,266
Would you look at that?

180
00:09:59,299 --> 00:10:02,235
I can stop time for ten seconds!

181
00:10:02,269 --> 00:10:04,638
All right, now that
i’ve defeated jotaro,

182
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:06,640
I should inspect
his lifeless body

183
00:10:06,673 --> 00:10:07,974
and drink his blood,

184
00:10:08,008 --> 00:10:10,444
that is, if there’s
any blood left to savor.

185
00:10:11,845 --> 00:10:14,481
( Grunting )

186
00:10:18,485 --> 00:10:19,987
This can’t be.

187
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:21,955
My body’s slowing down.

188
00:10:21,989 --> 00:10:23,657
What’s happening?

189
00:10:25,492 --> 00:10:29,463
n-no. It’s not
that i’m slowing down.

190
00:10:29,496 --> 00:10:32,766
For some reason,
I can’t move at all!

191
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:34,668
I don’t get it.

192
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:37,437
This is impossible.
i’m frozen.

193
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:40,407
Jotaro: Hey, dio,
it’s been 11 seconds.

194
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,976
i guess that’s
your stand’s limit, huh?

195
00:10:43,010 --> 00:10:46,380
Dio: Eh, what?!

196
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:49,249
Jotaro: I stopped time
at nine seconds,

197
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:51,018
and it’s a good thing I did.

198
00:10:51,051 --> 00:10:52,986
It gave me a chance to escape.

199
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,689
Good grief, you idiot.

200
00:10:55,722 --> 00:10:56,890
( Dio grunts )

201
00:10:56,924 --> 00:10:58,893
Jotaro: Here’s the thing.

202
00:10:58,926 --> 00:11:00,728
Since you’re frozen like that,

203
00:11:00,761 --> 00:11:03,364
destroying you
will only take a second!

204
00:11:03,397 --> 00:11:05,199
( Dio sputters )

205
00:11:05,232 --> 00:11:07,835
Jotaro!

206
00:11:09,903 --> 00:11:11,138
Dio: This is madness.

207
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:13,240
You can stop time, too?

208
00:11:13,273 --> 00:11:16,009
curse you!
This whole act was a ruse

209
00:11:16,043 --> 00:11:19,413
to waste my nine seconds,
wasn’t it, you bastard?

210
00:11:19,446 --> 00:11:22,282
Jotaro: How does it feel, dio?
Tell me.

211
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:23,617
( Dio sputters )

212
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,719
Jotaro: How’s it feel
having your archenemy

213
00:11:25,752 --> 00:11:28,388
tower behind you while you
stand frozen and helpless?

214
00:11:28,422 --> 00:11:30,090
I suppose it’s a lot

215
00:11:30,123 --> 00:11:31,691
like holding your breath
while underwater,

216
00:11:31,725 --> 00:11:35,229
only someone’s out to get you,
and your air is running out

217
00:11:35,262 --> 00:11:37,030
as you desperately swim
for your life.

218
00:11:37,064 --> 00:11:41,368
And then after finally reaching
the surface and taking a breath,

219
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:43,703
you get pulled right back in.

220
00:11:43,737 --> 00:11:46,039
Sound familiar?

221
00:11:46,073 --> 00:11:48,309
But after everything
you’ve done, dio,

222
00:11:48,342 --> 00:11:50,344
you’re not gonna get
any sympathy from me.

223
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:52,045
Star platinum: Ora!

224
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:53,314
( Dio groans )

225
00:11:53,347 --> 00:11:55,616
Jotaro: Time is about
to start moving again.

226
00:12:01,588 --> 00:12:04,558
( Dio gasping )

227
00:12:06,426 --> 00:12:09,462
Jotaro: Compassion is something
you’re never gonna get from me.

228
00:12:09,496 --> 00:12:13,233
I haven’t got any kindness
for your sorry undead ass,

229
00:12:13,267 --> 00:12:15,102
though I gotta admit

230
00:12:15,135 --> 00:12:18,438
you look pretty pathetic
writhing on the ground in agony.

231
00:12:18,472 --> 00:12:20,975
As much as I want to,
killing you like this

232
00:12:21,008 --> 00:12:23,143
would leave
a pretty bad taste in my mouth.

233
00:12:23,177 --> 00:12:26,547
i wonder how long
it’ll take for you to heal.

234
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:29,550
Three seconds? Four, maybe?

235
00:12:29,583 --> 00:12:31,652
The very moment
your legs are healed,

236
00:12:31,685 --> 00:12:35,088
star platinum’s headed your way
to demolish you.

237
00:12:35,122 --> 00:12:36,190
( Dio gasps )

238
00:12:36,223 --> 00:12:38,325
Jotaro: If this were
the wild west,

239
00:12:38,358 --> 00:12:41,194
the hero would say,
"it’s high noon.

240
00:12:41,228 --> 00:12:44,231
"Now get off the ground,
and draw your piece, dio.

241
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:45,532
You’re getting one shot."

242
00:12:48,368 --> 00:12:50,737
Dio: This insignificant whelp,

243
00:12:50,771 --> 00:12:53,140
how dare he mock me?!

244
00:12:53,173 --> 00:12:55,942
Though I shouldn’t be surprised.

245
00:12:55,976 --> 00:12:58,045
Of course he would use
this opportunity

246
00:12:58,078 --> 00:13:00,347
to make
such a human declaration.

247
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:01,681
( Laughs )

248
00:13:01,715 --> 00:13:04,518
You think like a true mortal,

249
00:13:04,551 --> 00:13:07,487
cursed with a fleeting life
destined for obscurity.

250
00:13:07,521 --> 00:13:10,391
A bad taste in your mouth,
you say?

251
00:13:10,424 --> 00:13:13,294
What, are you afraid
you’d regret killing me?

252
00:13:13,327 --> 00:13:17,131
That reasoning is as pathetic
as your species.

253
00:13:17,164 --> 00:13:20,100
Your foolish honor
will be your demise.

254
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,068
( Laughs )

255
00:13:22,102 --> 00:13:25,072
That is where you and I differ.

256
00:13:25,105 --> 00:13:29,710
My vision is clear, and my mind
is focused on a single goal.

257
00:13:29,743 --> 00:13:33,714
i want to dominate,
nothing more, nothing less.

258
00:13:33,747 --> 00:13:36,516
it’s the only thing
that will bring me fulfillment.

259
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:39,686
But how I go about doing that...

260
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:42,323
Doesn’t matter in the slightest!

261
00:13:44,057 --> 00:13:47,294
There! How about a little blood
in your eyes?!

262
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:50,096
I win! Die!

263
00:13:51,465 --> 00:13:53,634
Jotaro: Ora!

264
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:04,345
( Grunts )

265
00:14:04,378 --> 00:14:06,614
( Dio chuckles )

266
00:14:09,683 --> 00:14:10,651
( Gasps )

267
00:14:10,684 --> 00:14:12,719
♪

268
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:16,990
( Yelling )

269
00:14:17,024 --> 00:14:19,660
What the hell?!

270
00:14:20,694 --> 00:14:22,362
It’s impossible!

271
00:14:22,396 --> 00:14:25,466
I am the immortal dio!

272
00:14:25,499 --> 00:14:27,067
( Gurgles )

273
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:31,538
I am dio!

274
00:14:37,311 --> 00:14:41,348
Jotaro: When the sun comes up,
you’ll be nothing but dust.

275
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:45,485
You only made one mistake,
one that got you killed.

276
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:49,490
Dio, this whole thing might
have ended differently, but...

277
00:14:49,523 --> 00:14:51,592
You went and pissed me off.

278
00:14:51,625 --> 00:14:53,093
Was it worth it?

279
00:14:53,126 --> 00:14:55,061
♪

280
00:15:07,374 --> 00:15:08,675
( Sirens blaring )

281
00:15:17,117 --> 00:15:19,353
Driver: This is speedwagon
foundation, car two.

282
00:15:19,386 --> 00:15:22,756
We’re traveling northbound
on the al-nil expressway,

283
00:15:22,789 --> 00:15:24,357
and we’ve retrieved
dio’s remains.

284
00:15:24,391 --> 00:15:28,862
i repeat.
We’ve retrieved dio’s remains.

285
00:15:28,896 --> 00:15:31,599
man: Dio’s body is
showing cellular activity.

286
00:15:31,632 --> 00:15:34,068
He must be exposed
to sunlight immediately.

287
00:15:34,101 --> 00:15:35,636
Proceed with extreme caution!

288
00:15:35,669 --> 00:15:36,670
Driver: Roger.

289
00:15:37,838 --> 00:15:39,873
Man: Noriaki kakyoin is dead.

290
00:15:39,907 --> 00:15:41,876
his body
is being transported now.

291
00:15:41,909 --> 00:15:44,011
Jean Pierre polnareff
is unconscious.

292
00:15:44,044 --> 00:15:46,046
The medical staff
of car one has him.

293
00:15:46,079 --> 00:15:47,380
Driver: Roger.

294
00:15:47,414 --> 00:15:50,083
Man: Car two,
I have a question.

295
00:15:50,117 --> 00:15:52,720
Why have you placed
the remains of dio

296
00:15:52,753 --> 00:15:55,022
and Joseph joestar
in the same car?

297
00:15:56,256 --> 00:15:58,191
jotaro:
Because it’s not over yet.

298
00:15:58,225 --> 00:15:59,827
Dio borrowed something
from us...

299
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:01,228
Doctor: Eh?

300
00:16:01,261 --> 00:16:04,931
Jotaro: And we need to take it
back from the bastard.

301
00:16:04,965 --> 00:16:07,234
Doctor #2: I’m not following
your train of thought.

302
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:10,070
jotaro: I need you
to perform a blood transfusion

303
00:16:10,103 --> 00:16:11,237
between the two bodies.

304
00:16:11,271 --> 00:16:12,239
( Doctors gasp )

305
00:16:12,272 --> 00:16:13,940
Doctor #1: That’s absurd!

306
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:17,010
You want us to transfuse
dio’s blood into Mr. Joestar?

307
00:16:17,044 --> 00:16:19,847
Doctor #2: I see! You’re trying
to bring him back to life!

308
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,116
Jotaro: It hasn’t
been all that long

309
00:16:22,149 --> 00:16:24,652
since dio drained his blood.

310
00:16:24,685 --> 00:16:27,221
his upper half
was destroyed in the fight,

311
00:16:27,254 --> 00:16:29,857
but we’ll take
as much as we can.

312
00:16:29,890 --> 00:16:32,860
if we hurry,
I think we can make it.

313
00:16:32,893 --> 00:16:34,128
( Driver gasps )

314
00:16:34,161 --> 00:16:36,830
hey, car one,
did you catch all that? Over.

315
00:16:36,864 --> 00:16:37,865
( Man gasps ) Roger.

316
00:16:37,898 --> 00:16:39,333
Doctor #2: It’s impossible!

317
00:16:39,366 --> 00:16:41,268
- He doesn’t even have a pulse.
- Doctor #1: Right!

318
00:16:41,301 --> 00:16:42,869
not to mention
his heart has stopped,

319
00:16:42,903 --> 00:16:44,738
which means
we couldn’t circulate his blood

320
00:16:44,771 --> 00:16:47,173
- if we wanted to.
- Jotaro: Don’t give me that.

321
00:16:47,207 --> 00:16:50,944
You could call everything we’ve
done on this journey impossible.

322
00:16:50,978 --> 00:16:54,048
I’m tired of hearing words
like "impossible" or "futile."

323
00:16:54,081 --> 00:16:55,916
They all mean nothing to us.

324
00:16:55,949 --> 00:16:57,617
( Doctors stammer )

325
00:16:57,651 --> 00:16:59,786
jotaro: You can do it
if his heart’s beating, right?

326
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,755
- Well, you’re in luck.
- doctors: Huh?

327
00:17:01,788 --> 00:17:04,924
Jotaro: Thanks to dio, i’ve
already had a bit of practice

328
00:17:04,958 --> 00:17:07,227
with stopping
and starting hearts.

329
00:17:07,261 --> 00:17:09,130
Star platinum: Ora!

330
00:17:13,634 --> 00:17:15,069
Doctor #1: I hear a pulse.

331
00:17:15,102 --> 00:17:16,837
Doctor #2: Yes, you’re right!
His heart is beating!

332
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:18,238
Doctor #1: We have
to transfuse his blood

333
00:17:18,272 --> 00:17:19,807
into Mr. Joestar quickly!

334
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:22,009
doctor #2: We might
just be able to pull this off!

335
00:17:22,042 --> 00:17:24,778
♪

336
00:17:39,693 --> 00:17:41,361
( Gasps ) Remarkable!

337
00:17:41,395 --> 00:17:43,097
Take a look at his skin!

338
00:17:43,130 --> 00:17:45,399
It’s completely regaining
all its color!

339
00:17:47,401 --> 00:17:49,370
His skin is filling out!

340
00:17:49,403 --> 00:17:51,105
( Steady beeping )

341
00:17:51,138 --> 00:17:53,140
Doctor #1: My god!
Brain activity, too!

342
00:17:53,173 --> 00:17:54,875
Doctor #2: I don’t believe it.

343
00:17:54,908 --> 00:17:57,010
His vitals are stable as well!

344
00:17:58,979 --> 00:18:00,214
( Joseph sighs )

345
00:18:00,247 --> 00:18:01,548
- ( Doctors gasp )
- Doctor #2: His eyes!

346
00:18:01,582 --> 00:18:02,683
He opened his eyes!

347
00:18:02,716 --> 00:18:05,052
Doctor #1: We did it! He’s back!

348
00:18:05,085 --> 00:18:06,086
( Jotaro gasps )

349
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:08,188
( Joseph sighs )

350
00:18:10,257 --> 00:18:12,025
Jotaro: Old man?

351
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,595
( Joseph chuckles )

352
00:18:15,696 --> 00:18:16,897
( Jotaro gasps )

353
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,765
( Doctors gasp )

354
00:18:18,799 --> 00:18:22,670
( Joseph laughs )

355
00:18:22,703 --> 00:18:24,872
You’re a damn fool, jotaro.

356
00:18:24,905 --> 00:18:27,274
Jotaro: You have
got to be kidding!

357
00:18:27,307 --> 00:18:28,909
Joseph: Hmm.

358
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:31,878
all you’ve done
is resurrect yours truly!

359
00:18:31,912 --> 00:18:33,113
Jotaro: Bastard!

360
00:18:33,146 --> 00:18:34,914
Joseph: Wait! Calm down, jotaro!

361
00:18:34,948 --> 00:18:37,184
It was a joke!
I was just kidding!

362
00:18:37,217 --> 00:18:39,019
There’s no need to get violent!

363
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:40,020
( Jotaro groans )

364
00:18:40,053 --> 00:18:41,154
Joseph: I’m sorry!

365
00:18:41,188 --> 00:18:43,590
I was just trying
to have some fun!

366
00:18:43,624 --> 00:18:45,659
You have my word, it’s me!

367
00:18:45,692 --> 00:18:49,696
I’m Joseph joestar! I was
born September 27th in 1920!

368
00:18:49,730 --> 00:18:53,767
My wife’s name is Suzie q,
and I collect comics as a hobby!

369
00:18:54,902 --> 00:18:56,971
Jotaro: I have
a question for you.

370
00:18:57,004 --> 00:18:59,573
Who’s the leading actress
in "Tarzan, the ape man"?

371
00:18:59,606 --> 00:19:00,974
Joseph: Bo Derek.

372
00:19:01,008 --> 00:19:02,776
Jotaro: Okay,
now answer this one.

373
00:19:02,809 --> 00:19:05,078
Who sang "eat it,"
the spoof of "beat it"?

374
00:19:05,112 --> 00:19:06,780
Joseph: "Weird al" yankovic.

375
00:19:06,813 --> 00:19:09,582
Jotaro: Good grief,
it has to be you.

376
00:19:09,616 --> 00:19:11,852
Who else would know
pointless crap like that?

377
00:19:11,885 --> 00:19:12,886
( Joseph sighs )

378
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,889
Driver: This is car two. Over!

379
00:19:14,922 --> 00:19:18,025
it’s amazing!
Mr. Joestar is back with us!

380
00:19:18,058 --> 00:19:20,827
he’s come back
from the brink of death!

381
00:19:20,861 --> 00:19:24,198
It’s a miracle! Over!

382
00:19:24,231 --> 00:19:25,933
Jotaro: Hear that?

383
00:19:25,966 --> 00:19:30,571
We’ve taken back everything
you stole from us, dio.

384
00:19:30,604 --> 00:19:32,606
♪

385
00:19:59,132 --> 00:20:01,901
Joseph: It’s finally over.

386
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:09,943
Dio took something precious
from all of us.

387
00:20:09,977 --> 00:20:13,013
for a hundred years,
he’s taken whatever he wanted.

388
00:20:13,046 --> 00:20:17,150
His appetite for power
has been insatiable.

389
00:20:17,184 --> 00:20:20,788
Jotaro: He’s taken far too much.
You realize that.

390
00:20:20,821 --> 00:20:23,657
joseph: Yeah.
He’s taken things from us

391
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:26,793
that’ll we’ll never
be able to get back.

392
00:20:26,827 --> 00:20:29,296
The losses that we’ve endured
on this journey

393
00:20:29,329 --> 00:20:32,132
stretch as far
as the planet itself.

394
00:20:32,166 --> 00:20:35,169
But thanks to their sacrifices,

395
00:20:35,202 --> 00:20:38,739
we’re here to tell the tale
and carry on in their stead.

396
00:20:38,772 --> 00:20:40,007
( Jotaro sighs )

397
00:20:41,108 --> 00:20:46,013
Kakyoin, iggy, avdol...

398
00:20:47,181 --> 00:20:48,783
It’s over.

399
00:20:53,687 --> 00:20:55,322
( Overlapping chatter )

400
00:20:55,355 --> 00:20:57,357
Announcer: Passengers
awaiting incoming flights,

401
00:20:57,391 --> 00:20:59,326
please make your way
to the boarding gate.

402
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:01,962
Joseph: So you’re really going
back to France, polnareff?

403
00:21:01,995 --> 00:21:06,099
This may be a bit forward,
but your family’s gone.

404
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:09,069
Why don’t you come back
with me to New York?

405
00:21:10,404 --> 00:21:13,307
Polnareff: Mr. Joestar,
I know they’re gone,

406
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:16,109
but France is the only home
i’ve ever known.

407
00:21:16,143 --> 00:21:17,911
It’s filled with memories.

408
00:21:17,945 --> 00:21:21,382
It’s a place I must return to,
no matter where I go.

409
00:21:21,415 --> 00:21:24,785
But if you ever need anything,
all you have to do is call,

410
00:21:24,818 --> 00:21:26,386
and i’ll be there
in a heartbeat.

411
00:21:27,788 --> 00:21:29,189
Joseph: We’re gonna
miss you, buddy.

412
00:21:34,328 --> 00:21:37,364
Polnareff: It wasn’t easy,
that’s for damn sure,

413
00:21:37,397 --> 00:21:39,666
but I had a hell of a time,

414
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,169
and i’m lucky to have been
on this adventure with you guys.

415
00:21:42,202 --> 00:21:44,071
Jotaro: Hmm.

416
00:21:44,104 --> 00:21:46,907
Joseph: Remember, we’re a team,

417
00:21:46,940 --> 00:21:48,975
and that’s never gonna change.

418
00:21:50,177 --> 00:21:51,779
announcer:
Calling all passengers

419
00:21:51,812 --> 00:21:54,915
for France international
airlines, flight 92 to Paris.

420
00:21:54,948 --> 00:21:56,917
Please proceed to gate 18.

421
00:21:56,950 --> 00:21:59,619
Polnareff: A bientot,
you ornery bastard.

422
00:21:59,653 --> 00:22:01,188
Live long and happy.

423
00:22:01,221 --> 00:22:04,324
And you, his moody grandson,
you’d better not forget me.

424
00:22:04,358 --> 00:22:06,827
Jotaro: We’ll meet again,
that is, of course,

425
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:09,930
if you don’t hate my guts
by then, stubborn jackass!

426
00:22:09,963 --> 00:22:12,098
Joseph: We wouldn’t be able
to forget about you,

427
00:22:12,132 --> 00:22:14,267
even if we wanted to, polnareff.

428
00:22:14,301 --> 00:22:15,936
You be well.

429
00:22:17,871 --> 00:22:19,039
Polnareff: Au revoir.

430
00:22:19,072 --> 00:22:20,140
Joseph: Yeah.

431
00:22:20,174 --> 00:22:21,642
Jotaro: See you later.

432
00:22:25,279 --> 00:22:28,048
♪

433
00:22:35,389 --> 00:22:36,357
( Holly sighs )

434
00:22:36,390 --> 00:22:38,025
Suzie q: Holly!

435
00:22:38,058 --> 00:22:40,961
How are you sitting up straight
all of a sudden?

436
00:22:40,994 --> 00:22:42,629
Holly: I’m feeling much better.

437
00:22:42,663 --> 00:22:44,965
i’m not sure
how to put it into words.

438
00:22:44,998 --> 00:22:47,634
It’s as if we could
read each other’s minds.

439
00:22:47,668 --> 00:22:48,936
- Suzie q: What?
- Holly: Mom,

440
00:22:48,969 --> 00:22:51,004
I can feel that they’re
coming home to us!

441
00:22:52,739 --> 00:22:54,708
( Suzie q gasps )
holly!

442
00:22:54,741 --> 00:22:57,110
Holly: Papa and my jotaro!

443
00:22:57,144 --> 00:22:58,612
( Gasps )

444
00:22:58,645 --> 00:23:00,780
They’re coming home!

445
00:23:00,814 --> 00:23:02,816
( Jet engine roars )

446
00:23:04,918 --> 00:23:06,953
♪

447
00:23:08,322 --> 00:23:09,790
Joseph: Hmm?

448
00:23:11,325 --> 00:23:12,993
( Chuckles )

449
00:23:15,329 --> 00:23:17,298
( Jotaro chuckles )

450
00:23:30,143 --> 00:23:32,145
♪

